\sum^n_{i=1}{e^i/i}
f(x) = \sum_{i = 1}^n \frac{x^i}{i}
f(x):=\sum_{k=1}^nx^{k-1}=\sum_{k=0}^{n-1}x^k=\frac{1-x^{n-1}}{1-x}
\int f(x)\,dx=\sum_{k=1}^n\int x^{k-1}dx=\sum_{k=1}^n\frac{x^k}{k}\ldots
\sum_{i=1}^n \frac{{\rm e}^i}{i} = -\Phi \left( {{\rm e}},1,n \right)\; {{\rm e}^{n}}-\ln   \left( -{{\rm e}}+1 \right) +{\frac {{{\rm e}^{n}}}{n}}
